    "answer_id" : 19364722,
    "question_id" : 8453543,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can use the following command: <code>jar xf rt.jar</code></p>\n<p>Where <code>x</code> stands for extraction and the <code>f</code> would be any options that indicate that the JAR file from which files are to be extracted is specified on the command line, rather than through stdin.</p>\n"
